{
  "texts": [
    "Apart from being guaranteed to always exist, CE is attractive for multiple reasons.",
    "It seems to emerge in natural settings where NE does not (Hart and Mas-Colell 2000).",
    "79 Unlike NE, it is more apt to accommodate the role of external factors that are decisive for the outcome, e.g., by following the recommendations of trusted sources.",
    "From a moral perspective, CE captures many situations-e.g., in moral or legal rule-following-where it is clearly incentivized to not deviate from the prescribed action (e.g., following traffic rules).",
    "Last but not least, CE are easier to compute than NE."
  ]
}